
   -------------------------------------------------------------------------
   README for ~4Dgifts/examples/Fortran/defpat/showpat32 source code example
   -------------------------------------------------------------------------


    showpat32 is a program which displays a 32X32 pixel size bitmap pattern
    using the DEFPATTERN(3G) GL function.  This program can display 32X32 
    bitmap patterns created by editpat32.

    An example of a 32X32 pattern file is the file:

             example.pattern

    To invoke showpat32 with the above file execute:

             showpat32 example.pattern

    Any bitmap pattern made using editpat32 can be used as an input file
    argument to showpat32
